# Player Grouping Project Rules

## Commands

```bash
npm run dev          # Dev server (localhost:5173)
npm run dev:vercel   # Vercel dev with serverless
npm run build        # Production build
npm test             # Vitest + jsdom | npm test -- <pattern>
npm run lint         # ESLint
npm run deploy       # GitHub Pages
```

## Architecture

React 19 + TypeScript + Vite. Repository pattern with Supabase as primary data source.

**Repositories** (from `@/repositories`):
- `playerRepository` / `createPlayerRepository()` → Supabase (forced)
- `groupingRepository` / `createGroupingRepository()` → Supabase or SQLite fallback
- Match, PlayerMatchStats, SkillAdjustment, PlayerVideo repos

**Services** (`src/services/`): DatabaseService, AuthService, ChatService, AiService, MonitoringService, FeedbackService, RatingHistoryService, MatchAnalysisService, MatchImportService

**Path alias**: `@/` → `src/` (tsconfig + vitest)

## Routes & Components

| Route | View |
|-------|------|
| `/` | Chat (AI assistant) |
| `/players` | Player management |
| `/grouping` | Drag-and-drop grouping |

**Key**: ShellBar nav, shadcn/ui, controlled forms, Dialog workflows, `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for class merging.

## Database Schema

Tables: `players`, `player_skills`, `grouping_history`, `matches`, `player_match_stats`, `skill_adjustments`, `player_videos`. 19 skills in player_skills + position-weighted overall.

## Grouping Algorithm

`src/utils/groupingAlgorithm.ts`: `groupPlayers()`, `calculateBalance()`, `balanceTeams()`. Strategies: `balanced`, `position-balanced`, `random`. Legacy: `src/utils/basketballGroupingAlgorithm.ts`.

## Chat & AI

- **ChatService** (`src/services/chat-service.ts`): streaming, function calling
- **SQL Agent** (`src/lib/sql-agent/sql-query-agent.ts`): natural language → Supabase queries. Whitelist tables, SELECT only, max 100 rows.
- **API** (`/api/chat.ts`): SSE, SQL Agent, CORS, intent detection

Env: `VITE_ARK_API_KEY`, `VITE_BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY` (backend).

## shadcn/ui

Components in `src/components/ui/`. Copy-paste model. Prefer wrapper components over modifying ui/*. Use `buttonVariants` / `VariantProps` for variants.

## Tailwind v4

CSS-first, `@theme` in CSS. Semantic tokens: `bg-background`, `text-foreground`, `bg-muted`, `border-border`, `bg-primary`, `bg-destructive`.

## TypeScript

- Strict mode, no `any`; use `unknown` + type guards
- Interfaces for objects, types for unions
- `readonly` for immutables
- Discriminated unions for results
- `import type` when only types needed

## Environment

Required: `VITE_SUPABASE_URL`, `VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY`. Optional: `VITE_ARK_API_KEY`, `VITE_BRAVE_SEARCH_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`.

## Deployment

| Platform | Base | Note |
|----------|------|------|
| GitHub Pages | `/player-grouping/` | No serverless |
| Vercel | `/` | SQL Agent supported |
| Cloudflare Pages | `/` | env in dashboard |

## TypeScript Patterns

```typescript
// Type guards
function isPlayer(v: unknown): v is Player {
  return typeof v === 'object' && v !== null && 'id' in v && typeof (v as { id: unknown }).id === 'string';
}

// Discriminated union
type Result<T, E> = { success: true; data: T } | { success: false; error: E };

// forwardRef
const Input = React.forwardRef<HTMLInputElement, React.ComponentPropsWithoutRef<'input'>>(...)
```

## Important

- Supabase required for player data
- `VITE_BASE_URL=/player-grouping/` for GitHub Pages
- SQL Agent works on Vercel (serverless); not on GitHub Pages
- Setup: `src/test/setup.ts` for Vitest
- Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` for className merging
